# Ugra Core Rules

Read `AGENTS.md` and `docs/` before making changes.

## Intelligence belongs to Ugra, not LLM

- Planning, memory, personality, goals → `application/intelligence/`
- LLM is transport only → `infrastructure/llm/` via `CompletionGateway`
- Never put personality in system prompts — use `PersonalityEngine`

## Architecture

- Clean Architecture: domain → application → infrastructure → presentation
- New agents extend `IntelligenceAgent`, register in DI only
- Prompts in `prompts/{agent}/v{N}.yaml`, not in Python
- Decisions → `CognitionEngine` reasoning records
- Cross-agent communication → `EventBus`, not direct calls

## Code style

- Minimal diff, match existing conventions
- Unit tests for new business logic in `tests/unit/`
- No commits unless user asks
